Ferric salts (such as $\mathrm{FeCl}_3$ ) form Prussian blue (blue ppt or colouration) with potassium ferrocyanide.
$$
\begin{array}{r}
4 \mathrm{FeCl}_3+3 \mathrm{~K}_4\left[\mathrm{Fe}(\mathrm{CN})_6\right] \longrightarrow \underset{\substack{\text { Prussian blue } \\
\text { (ferric ferrocyanide) }}}{\mathrm{Fe}_4\left[\mathrm{Fe}(\mathrm{CN})_6\right]_3} \\
+12 \mathrm{KCl}
\end{array}
$$
